<item>
            <title>[LU-7849] Need to purge &quot;DLC&quot; naming from code and user-visible areas</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7849</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We really need to purge the &quot;DLC&quot; and &quot;Dynamic LNet Configuration&quot; terms from the code and from user visible interfaces, and from documentation.  &quot;DLC&quot; was a project to add new functionality, it should not be a name that ever gets embedded anywhere permanent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For instance, the autoconf function named LN_CONFIG_DLC should &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; have any reference to &quot;DLC&quot;.  The check is whether libyaml exists, and that is all that fuction needs to concern itself with.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The --disable-dlc option should almost certainly have another name as well.  From a user&apos;s standpoint, it would seem to primarily be about whether or not the &quot;lnetctl&quot; command gets built, so it might make a great deal more sense to name the option after lnetctl.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In any event, eventually lnet configuration will just by dynamic, and few users will not care that it wasn&apos;t in the past, and embedding the DLC project name everywhere will just be an anachronism.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
